      "titleArabic": "اسم الآلة",
      "content": [
        "Nouns of instrument (اسم الآلة) are derived from verbs to indicate the tool used to perform an action.",
        "There are three main patterns from classical Arabic and several modern patterns."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern مِفْعَال: مِفْتَاح (key), مِنْشَار (saw)",
        "Pattern مِفْعَل: مِبْرَد (file), مِشْرَط (scalpel)",
        "Pattern مِفْعَلَة: مِكْنَسَة (broom), مِطْرَقَة (hammer)",
        "Modern pattern فَعَّالَة: غَسَّالَة (washing machine)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "مِفْتَاحٌ", "english": "key (tool for opening)" },
        { "arabic": "مِقَصٌّ", "english": "scissors (tool for cutting)" },
        { "arabic": "مِنْشَارٌ", "english": "saw (tool for sawing)" },
        { "arabic": "مِكْنَسَةٌ", "english": "broom (tool for sweeping)" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Modern Patterns",
      "titleArabic": "الأوزان الحديثة",
      "content": [
        "Modern Arabic has developed additional patterns for naming machines and electrical devices.",
        "These patterns are widely accepted and commonly used in contemporary Arabic."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "فَعَّالَة: غَسَّالَة (washer), ثَلَّاجَة (refrigerator)",
        "فَاعُول: حَاسُوب (computer)",
        "مِفْعَل: مِصْعَد (elevator)",
        "فَاعِلَة: طَابِعَة (printer), شَاحِنَة (truck)"
      ],
      "examples": [
